# Clingy 4 U — Cursor Rules
# Read this before touching any file. Every session.

## Project
Clingy 4 U (working title: Sticky Bridges) is a mobile-first PWA that helps people make and keep plans together IRL. Every plan is a piece of gum. Completed plans form permanent bridges between people. Read PRD.md and DESIGN.md before writing any code.

## Stack
- React + Vite + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS (config in tailwind.config.js — use only defined tokens, never arbitrary values)
- Supabase (auth, database, realtime, edge functions, cron)
- react-force-graph-2d (network graph)
- Lucide React (icons, strokeWidth={1.75}, size 20-22px)
- Vercel (deployment)

## Commands
- `npm run dev` — start dev server
- `npm run build` — production build
- `npm run typecheck` — run TypeScript checker
- `npm run lint` — run ESLint
Always run typecheck after a series of changes. Fix all type errors before moving on.

## File structure
```
src/
  assets/
    gum/           ← SVG gum shape assets (gum-strip.svg, gum-ball.svg, gum-chiclet.svg, gum-block.svg, gum-blob.svg)
  components/
    ui/            ← reusable primitives (Button, Card, Tag, Input, BottomSheet)
    gum/           ← gum-specific components (GumPiece, GumPocket, GumBall)
    network/       ← graph components (NetworkGraph, BridgeDetail)
    feed/          ← feed components (PostCard, CommentList)
    layout/        ← Layout, BottomTabBar, PageHeader
  pages/           ← one file per route
  hooks/           ← custom React hooks (useAuth, useGumPieces, useConnections)
  lib/
    supabase.ts    ← supabase client
    categorizer.ts ← keyword matching logic
    constants.ts   ← category definitions, color map, shape list
  types/           ← TypeScript interfaces and types
  utils/           ← helper functions
```

## Code style
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Functional components only — no class components
- Named exports for components, default exports for pages
- Props interfaces defined above every component
- Async data fetching in custom hooks, not in components directly
- Error and loading states handled in every data-fetching hook
- No inline styles — Tailwind classes only
- Use CSS variables from DESIGN.md for any value not in Tailwind config

## Supabase conventions
- All DB calls go through typed supabase client
- Row Level Security is enabled on all tables — never disable it
- Edge functions live in `supabase/functions/`
- Never expose service role key to the client
- Use `supabase.auth.getUser()` not `getSession()` for auth checks

## Component conventions
- Every interactive element has a hover and active state
- Every async action has a loading state (disable button, show spinner)
- Every screen has an empty state — refer to DESIGN.md section 13 for copy
- Mobile-first — design for 390px, then scale up
- Always include `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)` padding on bottom-fixed elements

## Gum piece components
- Shapes are randomized at creation and stored in the DB — never re-randomize
- Color is always derived from category slug via the color map in constants.ts
- Wrapped/unwrapped state is a prop, not internal state
- The `gum-body` layer in each SVG uses `fill="var(--gum-color)"` — set via CSS custom property

## Categories (never hardcode these inline — import from constants.ts)
```ts
intimate  → #CF8EE8
active    → #7DD47A
playful   → #F07868
explore   → #6DB8F0
recharge  → #82C9A0
savor     → #F0A84A
support   → #E89AA8
```

## Animation
- Blob morph: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.2, 0.64, 1)
- Screen transitions: 250ms slide-up for push, slide-down for dismiss, fade for tabs
- Always wrap continuous animations in @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)
- Placeholder pieces (status: placeholder) get float animation class
- Active pieces get morph animation class
- Graveyard pieces get no animation, desaturated filter

## Slot logic (enforce server-side only — never trust client)
- Global limit: 25 active slots per user (placeholders + active combined)
- Per-pair limit: 5 active slots
- Check happens in edge function before piece creation or acceptance
- Client shows current count but never enforces the limit itself

## What not to do
- Never add features not in PRD.md — write them to BACKLOG.md instead
- Never use arbitrary Tailwind values (e.g. w-[347px]) — use design tokens
- Never store sensitive data in localStorage or client state
- Never skip loading and error states
- Never hardcode category colors — always derive from constants.ts
- Never add console.log to committed code
- Never modify the DB schema without updating PRD.md data model section
